    <abstract id="aspace_5544915b43128f33630c876f98059e53">Ives and Pierce, a rural business in Canaan, Connecticut, was owned by Henry B. Ives and Robert D. Pierce, and sold grain, chicken feed, poultry, and agricultural supplies to local farmers. The business also sold coal to local residents. The records consist of 36 volumes of financial journals, daybooks, and coal and account books.</abstract>
  </did>
  <bioghist id="aspace_18dddb369ba114008e0c34148da8510a">
    <head>History</head>
<p>Ives and Pierce, a rural business in Canaan, Connecticut, was owned by Henry B. Ives and Robert D. Pierce, and sold grain, chicken feed, poultry, and agricultural supplies to local farmers. The business also sold coal to local residents.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_0cb943e2344a80662add715d368c7ac7">
    <head>Scope and Content</head>
<p>The collection contains the financial and business records of Ives and Pierce.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <arrangement id="aspace_7596cef6efd66935c887e41aa3e794f1">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p><emph render="bold">Series I: Journals and Daybooks </emph> (1895-1929) consists of thirty journals and four daybooks which list daily sales made at the store. The entries include the transaction date, the customer's name, a description of the item sold, and the purchase price.</p><p><emph render="bold">Series II: Coal and Account Books </emph> (1900-1928) consists of two volumes. The first volume lists sales of coal for 1922 to 1928. The second volume is an account book, 1900-1925, which records coal and grain purchased.</p>  </arrangement>
